> Some people prefer chicken breast, but at HelloFresh, we're 'Team Thigh'. Not only
> are they juicier, but they are also packed with more flavour than your standard breast
> due to their high fat content, making this linguine the ultimate taste sensation.

Preheat your oven to 200°C. Put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil with a pinch
of @salt{pinch} for the pasta. Chop the @British streaky bacon{4} into 1cm wide strips
(you can use scissors!). Halve the @onion{1/2} through the root, peel then slice into
thin half moons. Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the bacon
and cook until crispy, stirring occasionally, ~{5%minutes}. While the bacon cooks,
spread the @broccoli florets{200} on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}, a
pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Set aside.

Once the bacon is cooked, add the @diced chicken thigh{260} to the pan (pop it back
on medium high heat) and season with a pinch of salt and black pepper. Cook until
browned, ~{5%minutes}.

> TIP: You may need to do this in batches - you want the chicken to brown, not stew.

Add the onion and cook until soft, ~{5%minutes}. If the onion browns, that's fine,
it will just add to the flavour!

Roast the broccoli on the top shelf of your oven until crispy, ~{12-15%minutes},
shaking the tray halfway through cooking. At the same time, add the
@linguine{200} to your pan of boiling water and cook, ~{11-12%minutes}. Once cooked,
drain in a #colander{} and return it to the pan (off the heat). Drizzle with a little
@olive oil{} to stop the pasta sticking together.

Add the @water{100} and @chicken stock powder{1/2} to the chicken mixture. Stir to
dissolve the stock and then bubble away for ~{5%minutes}. Stir to make sure you get
all the yummy meaty bits from the bottom of the pan. Add the @creme fraiche{100} to
the pan, mix well in and bring back to the boil. Simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}, then
remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Add the drained pasta to the sauce along with half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40}. Toss it together (or just stir!). Season with a good pinch of salt and black
pepper. Serve the chicken linguine in bowls with the roasted broccoli on top.
Sprinkle over the remaining cheese and parsley - or not, if the kids aren't keen!
Enjoy!